President Biden has declared a major disaster in the state of Utah due to flooding that occurred from May 1 to May 27, 2023. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures on a cost-sharing basis. Jon K. Huss of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.